                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.105/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 20, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 11:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66. Referring to my telegram No. 61, June 18, the final report of the Board of
                    Investigation completely cleared Aarons of the charges against him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
